<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A183BF4CDECA" blockId="17.[211,1172,168,295]" box="[211,319,168,191]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<heading id="466581BA0E572D2AFF19A183BF4CDECA" box="[211,319,168,191]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273" reason="5">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A183BF4CDECA" box="[211,319,168,191]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A1E4BAE0DF52" blockId="17.[211,1172,168,295]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<taxonomicName id="DA924D550E572D2AFF19A1E4BC7FDE92" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1944" box="[211,524,207,231]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachoensis" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A1E4BF26DE92" box="[211,341,207,231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Leptochirus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFEA3A1FBBF08DE92" box="[361,379,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFE5DA1E4BC7FDE92" box="[407,524,207,231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">pachoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFD86A1FBBC16DE92" box="[588,613,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">L.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DA924D550E572D2AFDBAA1E4BC98DE92" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1903" box="[624,747,207,231]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFDB2A1FBBCF9DE92" box="[632,650,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFD6DA1E4BC98DE92" box="[679,747,207,231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the accessory tooth of the left mandible far from the lateral longitudinal ridge (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFD3FA1C4BDF8DF72" box="[757,907,239,263]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 3A, E</figureCitation>
), but 
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFC06A1DBBDADDF72" box="[972,990,240,263]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">L</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="DA924D550E572D2AFC21A1C4BAE0DF72" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1944" box="[1003,1171,239,263]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachoensis" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFC3EA1DBBA75DF72" box="[1012,1030,240,263]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFBD4A1C4BAE0DF72" box="[1054,1171,239,263]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">pachoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the first dorsal tooth of the left mandible bifurcate (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFBD9A024BAF4DF52" box="[1043,1159,271,295]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 3E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5588655D0E572D2AFF19A047BF9FD8D3" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273" type="description">
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A047BF21DFF6" blockId="17.[211,438,364,427]" box="[211,338,364,387]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<heading id="466581BA0E572D2AFF19A047BF21DFF6" box="[211,338,364,387]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273" reason="5">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A047BF21DFF6" box="[211,338,364,387]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A0BFBFC5DFDE" blockId="17.[211,438,364,427]" box="[211,438,403,427]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">BL: 14.73; BW: 2.46</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A0F8BDEEDF9E" blockId="17.[211,925,467,491]" box="[211,925,467,491]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Body strongly depressed. Body all black except tarsi red-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A338BFB2DD3F" blockId="17.[211,1172,531,842]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A338BF64DC5E" bold="true" box="[211,279,531,555]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Head.</emphasis>
Transverse (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFE6EA338BC69DC5E" box="[420,538,531,555]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
). Inner lateral teeth separated by a depression extending to base. Inner and outer lateral teeth fused and resembling a septum; median sulcus deep, sides of median sulcus parallel; laterofrontal depressions oval. Labrum with outer edge strongly angled and lateral-apical edge concave. Mandibles (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFC2FA359BA12DCFF" box="[997,1121,626,650]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figures 2E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFBA1A359BAF8DCFF" box="[1131,1163,626,650]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">3E</figureCitation>
) with lateral longitudinal ridge occupying less than two-thirds of apical region; external margin strongly developed, attenuated anteriorly. Left mandible (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFC64A399BA53DCBF" box="[942,1056,690,714]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 3E</figureCitation>
) with first dorsal tooth developed, straight and bifurcate, accessory tooth far from lateral longitudinal ridge; second dorsal tooth little developed and resembling a small hill; first ventral tooth with tooth accessory pointed. Submentum with setae arranged in row on anterolateral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A25ABFFBDADD" blockId="17.[211,1172,881,1192]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A25ABF5EDDFC" bold="true" box="[211,301,881,905]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFE7CA25ABC5BDDFC" box="[438,552,881,905]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
) a little wider than long (PL: 2.54; PW: 2.98); superior marginal line of hypomeron not interrupted, not bent to dorsal region at anterior margin and bent to slightly dorsal region at posterior margin; without pair of small depressions near basal constriction. Inferior marginal line of hypomeron reaching anterior margin. Apex of prosternal process strongly expanded and resembling a circular plate, extending considerably beyond the lateral process of hypomeron. Metaventrite with microsculpture longitudinally undulate in median region and with small longitudinal median depression near posterior edge. Mesoscutellum with apex rounded. Elytra longer than broad and without pair of small depressions on posterior-lateral edge (EL: 3.27, EW: 2.95).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A5FBBF9CDB3D" blockId="17.[211,1172,1232,1352]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A5FBBF31DA9D" bold="true" box="[211,322,1232,1256]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Cylindrical. Sternite III with keel of apex rounded. Tergite IX (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFBD7A5FBBAF8DA9D" box="[1053,1163,1232,1256]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 6J</figureCitation>
) sclerotized with left and right plates separated, each with six or seven setae of various lengths. Tergite X (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFE6CA43BBC61DB5D" box="[422,530,1296,1320]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 6J</figureCitation>
) membranous except for sclerotized apical part, with two pairs of long apical setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A45BBD9AD852" blockId="17.[211,1172,1392,1575]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A45BBF67DBFD" box="[211,276,1392,1416]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Male.</emphasis>
Sternite IX (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFE63A45BBC53DBFD" box="[425,544,1392,1416]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 6K</figureCitation>
) composed of two plates, distal plate sclerotized except for membranous apex, anterior margin rounded, posterior margin sinuated and with two long setae; proximal plate less sclerotized, greater than apical, broadened in middle and with a projecting angle at posterior border. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFCA0A4E4BD8BDB92" box="[874,1016,1487,1511]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 6G–I</figureCitation>
) with median lobe slightly bulbous at base, pointed at apex, weakly sclerotized on dorsal side and a small plate sclerotized on ventral side; parameres short, fused dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D2D36D60E572D2AFF19A764BF9FD8D3" blockId="17.[211,1172,1615,1702]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">
<emphasis id="2FE6EAC40E572D2AFF19A764BF5AD812" box="[211,297,1615,1639]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male, except for the gonocoxites divided longitudinally (
<figureCitation id="85A92A530E572D2AFBD9A764BAF4D812" box="[1043,1159,1615,1639]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="15.[211,278,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 6. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) milton sp. nov. holotype: (A) aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) pachoensis. (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) proteus. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="17" pageNumber="1273">Figure 6L</figureCitation>
). The distal plate with apex membranous and long seta; proximal plate with the posterior region pointed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
